Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Pop the chunks on a low sided wide #baking tray{} in a single layer. Drizzle with @oil{}(a drizzle), then season with @salt{to taste} and @black pepper{to taste}. Toss to coat, then spread out. Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn halfway through cooking.

> Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, roughly chop @chives{1%bunch}. Zest the @lemon{1/2}(zested and cut into quarters) and cut into quarters. Peel and grate the @garlic{1%clove}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Divide any large @broccoli florets{200%g} into smaller pieces and pop onto a baking tray. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with @salt{to taste} and @black pepper{to taste}. Toss to coat.

When the potatoes have been in the oven for ~{15%minutes}, pop the broccoli onto the middle shelf of your oven to roast until crispy and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

8 mins before the potatoes are cooked. Put a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}. Add the @unsalted butter{30%g} to the pan and allow to melt. Season the @sea bass fillets{2} with @salt{to taste} and @black pepper{to taste} and once hot, carefully place your sea bream in the pan, skin side down and cook for ~{3-4%minutes} before turning over and cooking for ~{2-3%minutes} on the other side.

> In order to get crispy skin on the fish, don't move it around when it's cooking skin side down!

Add the chives and garlic to the pan with the fish and squeeze in half the lemon juice. Spoon the lemony garlicky chivey butter over the fish for ~{1-2%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

> The fish is cooked when it is opaque in the centre.

Divide the broccoli, and potatoes among the plates along with the buttery sea bream. Pour the butter sauce over the fish. Serve with the lemon zest sprinkled over and remaining lemon wedges alongside for squeezing over. Enjoy!